[[en:List of Shikinaisha in Hyūga Province]] [[sn:List of Shikinaisha in Hyuga Province]] [[ja:日向国の式内社一覧]] [[sn:List of Shikinaisha in Hyūga Province]] [[sn:日向国の式内社一覧]] [[de:List of Shikinaisha in Hyuga Province]][[Category:Shikinaisha bottom]][[Category:Shikinaisha bottom]] [[Category:qq]][[sn:List of Shikinaisha in Hyūga Province]][[Category:qq]] {{List of Shikinai Shrines}} {{translated page|ja|日向国の式内社一覧|version=57670601|comment=Imported full ja history}}

This is a '''List of Shikinaisha in Hyūga Province'''. Or the list of shrines in [[Hyūga Province]] which is present in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|12=draft}}. On this page we will also cover the {{ill|Shikigeisha|ja|式外社|1=Shikigeisha|12=draft}} of [[Hyūga Province]] which are shrines that are known to have existed at that time due to other historical records, such as the [[Rikkokushi]], but for some reason were excluded from the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|12=draft}}. We will cover them in a separate list to avoid confusion.
